        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>213</citedRange> (no image)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>102800</citedRange></bibl>. 
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#parisipresicce1990"/>, p. <citedRange>125</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="divine" ref="#Apollo"><name nymRef="#Ἀπόλλων">Ἀπώλλωνος</name></persName> 
                    <space quantity="2" unit="character"/> 
                    <persName type="divine" ref="#Panakeia"><name nymRef="#Πανάκεια">Πανακείας</name></persName> 
                    <space quantity="2" unit="character"/>  
                    <persName type="divine" ref="#Aphrodite"><name nymRef="#Ἀφροδίτα">Ἀφροδίτας</name></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Autels d'</supplied> Apollon, de Panakeia, d'Aphrodite.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Altars of</supplied> Apollo, of Panakeia, of Aphrodite.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Altari di</supplied> Apollo, di Panakeia, di Afrodite.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>About the clearance of the area and the discovery of the group of altars (<ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr102900</ref>,  <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr103000</ref>, 
                    <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr103200</ref>, <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr103300</ref>, <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr103400</ref>, <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr103430</ref>) 
                    see <bibl><ptr target="#parisipresicce1990"/></bibl> and now also <bibl><ptr target="#luni2014b"/>, p. <citedRange>141</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
